      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "RING (1) pinged the lids and led throughout to score last start (21.76) at Ballarat in Restricted WIN over 390m. Hard to fault recent form and looks a key chance again. CHEEKY ALESSIA (2) is a talented dog who hit the ground running from the stripes and led throughout to score (23.25) at Horsham in Grade 5 over 410m. Brilliant beginner who should be leading the way here. Has a strong record out of this box with two wins and a minor placing from three starts. Can measure up again. FOXY JAY (8) had the drop on the lead and went on to be beaten 4.5 lengths into second (22.22) at this track in a Grade 4/5 over 390m. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and three minor placings to her credit. Overdue and expected to feature again. WHIPSTICK SERENA (6) picked up a cheque last time and is in the mix again.",
